      "level": 1,
      "text": "Fuel pressure regulator removal and installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fire is strictly prohibited. ​",
        "Removal should be performed with the engine stopped and the battery (-) terminal disconnected. ​"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Fuel pump removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000488",
          "label": "Fuel pump removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Fuel pressure regulator removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "485_3.0_jpn_11582607_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the reservoir (A) and remove the pressure regulator (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Parts supplied as a set, including O-rings, must be replaced upon disassembly.",
        "Lubricate the O-ring with engine oil (genuine Honda) and install the O-ring with care to avoid binding. Never apply brake fluid, radiator fluid, vegetable or alcohol based oil or grease."
      ]
    }
  ],
